540  // we think of F as two dimensional vector space
541  // over f with basis (1,alpha)
542  // for i,j \in f, with x = i + j * alpha \in F, we have
543  // pair_embedding[i * q + j] = x;
544  // also,
545  // components[x * 2 + 0] = i;
546  // components[x * 2 + 1] = j;
547  // also, for i \in f, embedding[i] is the element
548  // in F that corresponds to i
549  // components[Q * 2]
550  // embedding[q]
551  // pair_embedding[q * q]

2554  // if u is singular and v \in \la u \ra^\perp, then
2555  // \pho_{u,v}(x) := x + \beta(x,v) u - \beta(x,u) v - Q(v) \beta(x,u) u
2556  // is called the Siegel transform (see Taylor p. 148)
2557  // Here Q is the quadratic form and \beta is the corresponding bilinear form

6723  // number of candidates (or objects) that we will test

6728  // type_of[N]

6732  // the classification of type_of[N]
6733  // this will be computed in finalize()

6737  // in which they appear in the list of candidates
